The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Vettori spell puts NZ on top
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Vettori spell puts NZ on top
                      
	Dhaka: New Zealand skipper Daniel Vettori took three Bangladesh wickets in one over at the fag end of the day as the hosts slumped to 13 for three at the close of the fourth day of the rain-affected second Test against on Tuesday.         
	New Zealand declared their first innings on 262 for six, midway through the final session with Jesse Ryder (91) and Brendon McCullum (66) hitting half-centuries.         
